/* file2.c */
int32_t ABC = 0;

In the following example, the implementation in question supports 31 signi ﬁ cant case-sensitive
character s in identiﬁ ers that do not have external linkage.
The identi ﬁ er engine_exhaust_gas_temperature_local is compliant with this rule. Although
it is not distinct from the identi ﬁ er engine_exhaust_gas_temperature_raw, it is in a di ﬀ erent
scope. However, it is not compliant with Rule 5.3.
